args: Now then. Do you all know why\nI called you all here today?
Guys, she's real angry for some reason,\nso just pretend you know why!
Well, that could not have been a more\nham-handed display if you tried. I will\njust have to speak to each of you in turn.
First, Sha Wujing. You were testing out\na new weapon in the courtyard, yes?
Well, yeeeees...but the courtyard is just\nso SPACIOUS! I couldn't help myself!
Yes. You can. Ever since you came to the\nHalidom, I've received complaints from\nCleo about your burning the laundry.
The courtyard is a shared space.\nIf you wish to use it, you must ensure\nyou do not bother others in so doing.
I've heard complaints that you have\nbeen breaking practice dummies\nwith your axe during training.
Well, yeah...but there's no point if you\ndon't go all-out when you train! No one's\ngonna get better otherwise.
For a seasoned warrior like you, perhaps.\nBut for beginners, drilling the basics\nslowly and carefully is how you grow.
Either way, it would be greatly appreciated\nif you stopped breaking castle fixtures.
And finally, Wu Kong. You were soaring\nabout causing mischief on the Jindou Yun\nlast night, weren't you?
Huh? No! I never did that!
Of course it is! It's a big fat truth!
So someone else was soaring above\nthe village yelling ＂Wu Kong is in\nthe HOOOOUSE!＂ last night?
No! I said something totally different!
Pfffft... Bwaaaa ha ha ha!\nDid you hear that, Sha Wujing?\nHe confessed on his own!
Hee hee! Wu Kong truly is a fool to have\nfallen for such a simple leading question.
Wu Kong, it seems I need to punish you\nfor trying to hide your wicked deed.\nOh ho ho ho...
O power universal of the Qilin,\nbe bound by my solemn decree!\nWealth of brilliance, ring of the sun...
Whoa! Master, wait! WHOA!\nThat's the Xihe incantation!
I am simply shining some light on your\nmisdeeds. Are you sorry for what you did?
Man, your punishments have really gone\noff the charts since you got that Xihe.
I am keeping its power under control.\nYou would not have emerged unscathed \nhad I unleashed its full potential.
Still, it's pretty weird to see you walking\naround with a relic that controls the chi\nof light.
Back when we were traveling together,\nyou always said stronger relics should be\nsealed away as soon as they were found.
And that has not changed. While strong\nrelics can be useful, they come with\nmore danger the stronger they are.
Okay, but why'd you decide to just\nstart struttin' around with one?
This is a special exception.\nThere were...circumstances.
They must have been one hell of a set of\ncircumstances to get you to cast your\n＂hey, let's seal everything＂ bit aside.
Is the Xihe's power truly so\nterrifying to you?
What? No! I ain't scared of nothin'!

Ah, I see. Well in that case, let me put
your mind at ease: I will not permit the
Xihe to rage out of control, even if doing
so comes at the cost of my life.
I-I told you, I'm not scared! I'm just...\nAaaand, she's gone.
Bwa ha ha! She did a hell of a tap dance\naround that question, didn't she?
Hey, no need to get all huffy.\nMakes sense she won't talk about it.
She's the one always scolding people not\nto act recklessly, so it's probably extra\nhard for her to tell you her reasons.
I bet you know why she's doing it, huh?
Sure I do. Hell, I was there\nwhen she got the thing.
Heh. You that worried about her?
I mean...yeah, I guess I am. That relic is\ncrazy strong, and it's a heavy burden for\nanyone to carry.
I just don't get why she won't seal it!\nI know she could have done so a hundred\ntimes by now, but she won't.
Guess you can't help but worry about your\nteacher. All right, fine. I'll tell you.\nBut it ain't exactly a fun tale.
She took a burden on herself again.\nThat's all this story is, in the end...
